Routes and JSON Schemas

Versioning and Paths
- Public API routes live under /api/v1/. Ops/meta may be top-level as in health/version.

Schema Requirements
- Provide schema: summary, description, tags.
- Validate input: querystring/params/body with JSON Schema. Set additionalProperties: false where applicable.
- Define response schemas for all expected codes (at least 200). Include required fields.

Handler Shape
- Prefer: async (request, reply) => { return { ... } } and let Fastify serialize JSON.
- Default inputs via nullish coalescing (??) and defaults in schema.

Tags
- Use domain tags for features (e.g., ‘hello’). Keep ‘ops’ for health/version, ‘meta’ for docs/openapi.